title: Existence of hyperbolic triangles
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A hyperbolic triangle with side lengths $$a,b,c\in \Bbb R^2$$ exists if and only if the triangle inequalities are satisfied.

A hyperbolic triangle with angles $$\alpha,\beta,\gamma\in{]0,\pi[}$$ exists if and only if

$$
\alpha+\beta+\gamma<\pi.
$$